    <field id="homePageContent" text-type="text/html">&lt;h1 id="polarion_wiki macro name=module-workitem;params=id=EL-12717"&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;div id="polarion_wiki macro name=module-workitem;params=id=EL-12718"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="polarion_wiki macro name=module-workitem;params=id=EL-12719"&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p id="polarion_1" class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"&gt;This document describes the system architecture and design considerations for the project. It covers requirements, technical specifications, and implementation guidelines that must be followed throughout the development lifecycle. The content has been reviewed by multiple stakeholders and represents the agreed-upon approach for delivering the solution.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p id="polarion_2" class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"&gt;Each section below contains structured information about a specific work item, including its description, linked items, and associated metadata. Readers should consult the index for navigation and refer to the appendix for additional context where needed.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p id="polarion_3" class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"&gt;The methodology applied here follows industry best practices and aligns with internal quality standards. Any deviations from these standards should be documented separately and submitted for review through the established change-control process.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p id="polarion_4" class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"&gt;Please note that all measurements are given in metric units unless otherwise specified. Diagrams included in this document are illustrative and not necessarily drawn to scale. For precise dimensions, refer to the official engineering drawings stored in the repository.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p id="polarion_5" class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"&gt;Comments and feedback on this document can be submitted through the usual review channels. All contributions are tracked and addressed in subsequent revisions, with the current version history available at the end of this document for reference.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="polarion_wiki macro name=module-workitem;params=id=EL-12720"&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p id="polarion_6" class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"&gt;The purpose of this document is to provide a clear and comprehensive description of the features that must be considered when applying the system in real-world scenarios. It is intended for engineers, project managers, and quality assurance personnel.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p id="polarion_7" class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"&gt;Additional considerations include compliance with applicable regulations, alignment with organizational goals, and integration with existing infrastructure components. Each of these aspects is examined in detail in the corresponding sections.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p id="polarion_8" class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"&gt;The remainder of this document is organized into thematic sections that progressively build on the concepts introduced here. Cross-references are provided where appropriate to help readers navigate between related topics without losing context.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="polarion_wiki macro name=module-workitem;params=id=EL-12721"&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p id="polarion_9" class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"&gt;This is the work item description. The following paragraph contains a long sentence that must remain on the current page if there is enough vertical space for it, even though a table follows immediately afterwards. The system should not pull this text onto the next page just because the table that comes next does not fit on the current page. The sentence should stay where it is, and the table should move to the next page on its own.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div id="polarion_wiki macro name=module-workitem;params=id=EL-12722"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div id="polarion_wiki macro name=module-workitem;params=id=EL-12723"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="polarion_wiki macro name=module-workitem;params=id=EL-12724"&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p id="polarion_11" class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"&gt;Another paragraph that should stay in place. If you see this text floating alone at the top of a new page with the previous page mostly empty, the page-break rules are still pulling content together incorrectly. The fix should keep this paragraph next to the preceding heading and let the table below find its own natural break point.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div id="polarion_wiki macro name=module-workitem;params=id=EL-12725"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="polarion_wiki macro name=module-workitem;params=id=EL-12726"&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p id="polarion_13" class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"&gt;This paragraph also precedes a single-row table. The expected behavior is that this text fills the available space on the current page, and if the table does not fit, only the table moves to the next page. The sentence here is intentionally long enough to make the layout decision visible during testing on different paper sizes.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div id="polarion_wiki macro name=module-workitem;params=id=EL-12727"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="polarion_wiki macro name=module-workitem;params=id=EL-12728"&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p id="polarion_15" class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"&gt;When testing this document, use the print preview and check that text near the bottom of each page stays in place. Pages should be filled from top to bottom without large empty areas above tables. If a table cannot fit on the current page, only the table should move forward — the paragraph above it should remain.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div id="polarion_wiki macro name=module-workitem;params=id=EL-12729"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p id="polarion_template_1"&gt;THIS DOCUMENT HAS NO CONTENT YET.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p id="polarion_template_2"&gt;YOU CAN CREATE AND SAVE CONTENT NOW USING THIS EDITOR.&lt;/p&gt;</field>
